-- India Is `Actively Considering' Imposing Import Tax on Sugar, Pawar Says
-- Pratik Parija
-- 2010-07-09T05:34:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/india-is-actively-considering-imposing-import-tax-on-sugar-pawar-says.html

          
          
             India, the world’s largest sugar
user, is “actively considering” imposing tax on imports of the
commodity, Farm Minister Sharad Pawar said in a copy of a speech
prepared for delivery at a conference in New Delhi.  
 The government may end stock limits for bulk consumers of
sugar, he said.  
